# KVPrimaryFunLearning Three.js Scene Rule

## Visual quality baseline
- Use stylized low-poly direction with consistent color management (`outputColorSpace = SRGB`, `ACESFilmic`).
- Prefer `MeshStandardMaterial`/PBR tuning in stylized ranges (higher roughness, moderate metalness) unless effect requires otherwise.
- Use layered lighting (ambient + hemisphere + key directional + optional rim/fill) to avoid flat or overly dark scenes.
- For hero moments, use controlled post-processing bloom via `EffectComposer`; keep strengths moderate in idle state.

## Performance and memory
- Keep `renderer.setPixelRatio(Math.min(window.devicePixelRatio, 2))`.
- Avoid per-frame object creation inside loops; reuse vectors/materials where practical.
- Implement full disposal: cancel RAF, remove listeners, dispose composer/renderer/geometries/materials/textures.
- Keep shadow quality balanced (`PCFSoftShadowMap`, practical map sizes, bias to reduce acne).

## Gameplay integration
- Scene class must expose explicit hooks for gameplay (`onCorrect...`, `onWrong...`, `onCompleted...`) used by `play.ts`.
- Every correct answer should trigger immediate visual change; completion state must be clearly visible and celebratory.
- Keep status text and scene progression synchronized (e.g., `x/y` progress and completion message).

## Validation checklist before done
- `npm run build` passes.
- Edited scene files show no new lints.
- Dev server responds (`HTTP 200`) and no new runtime errors appear in active terminal logs.
